</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1323,743,1329]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Diagnosis. 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[398,614,743,769]" pageId="13" pageNumber="22" refString="Razowski, J. (1999 c) Euliini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) of Chile. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 68, 69 - 90." type="journal article" year="1999" yearSuffix="c">
Razowski (
<number box="[532,593,743,769]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1999.0">1999</number>
c)
</bibRefCitation>
initially included three species in 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1182,743,768]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Haemateulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1182,743,768]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Haemateulia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematitis">
<emphasis box="[1200,1322,743,768]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">haematitis</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski" authorityName="Razowski" box="[406,629,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galenia">
<emphasis box="[406,494,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">galenia</emphasis>
Razowski
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1824" box="[708,971,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Peronea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acmanthes">
<emphasis box="[708,833,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">acmanthes</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown" box="[990,1179,783,809]" pageId="13" pageNumber="21" refString="Brown, J. W. (2000 b) Acmanthina: a new genus of tortricid moths (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) from Chile and Argentina. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 108, 106 - 113." type="journal article" year="2000" yearSuffix="b">
Brown (
<number box="[1094,1156,783,809]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2000.0">2000</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName authority="Curtis, 1824" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1824" box="[264,389,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Peronea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acmanthes">
<emphasis box="[264,389,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">acmanthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[431,572,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acmanthina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,572,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Acmanthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and above we transferred 
<taxonomicName box="[900,988,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galenia">
<emphasis box="[900,988,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">galenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1176,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1176,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Ptychocroca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As defined herein, 
<taxonomicName box="[353,505,863,888]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Haemateulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[353,505,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Haemateulia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick" box="[647,933,863,889]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematitis">
<emphasis box="[647,806,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. haematitis</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski and Gonzalez." authorityName="Razowski and Gonzalez." class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Haemateulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barrigana">
<emphasis box="[992,1147,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. barrigana</emphasis>
Razowski and González.
</taxonomicName>
Male genitalia of the two are characterized by a moderately short uncus, long, broad socii (extending beyond the gnathos tip), a rounded­rectangular valva, and a long, slender, curved aedeagus without cornuti (
<figureCitation box="[768,912,983,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="25.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,333,1667]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[313,1273,326,1670]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Male genitalia of Haemateulia and Acmanthina; valvae spread, aedeagus removed (to left of capsule). 10, H. haematitis; 11, H. barrigana 12, A. albipuncta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156578/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 10, 11</figureCitation>
). A short process subdistally from the venter of the gnathos arms and a moderately large, rectangular membranous region at the base of the valva appear to represent synapomorphies for the genus. Males of the two species are easily distinguished by the shape of the antenna (strongly serrate in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematitis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. haematitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and simple in 
<taxonomicName box="[485,641,1143,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Haemateulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barrigana">
<emphasis box="[485,641,1143,1168]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. barrigana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the weakly undulate venter and costa of the valva in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematitis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. haematitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both of which are nearly evenly curved in 
<taxonomicName box="[902,1056,1183,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Haemateulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barrigana">
<emphasis box="[902,1056,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. barrigana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the finely setose sacculus of 
<taxonomicName box="[402,560,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematitis">
<emphasis box="[402,560,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. haematitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(smooth in 
<taxonomicName box="[701,855,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Haemateulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barrigana">
<emphasis box="[701,855,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. barrigana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Females are characterized by a broad, evenly sclerotized plate surrounding the ostium and a deep notch at the posterior edge of tergum 
<number box="[354,370,1303,1329]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
, both of which appear to represent synapomorphies for the genus (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1295,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 27" captionStartId="28.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[335,1269,326,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[313,1273,326,1670]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 27. Female genitalia of Haemateulia, Acmanthina, Apotomops, and Bonagota. 22, H. haematitis. 23, H. barrigana; 24, Acmanthina acmanthes; 25, Apotomps boliviana; 26, Apotomops spomotopa; 27, Bonagota arizonae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156581/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 22, 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
